<h1>Ropework</h1>

<ol type=1><p>

<li>Explain the following:
<ol type=a>
<li>The development of ropes
<li>Kinds of ropes and their uses
<li>How to take care of ropes
<li>The weakening effects of knots</ol><p>

<li>Show how to tie the following knots, and explain their uses:
<ol type=a>
<li>Square Knot
<li>Fisherman's Knot
<li>Sheet Bend (Weaver's Knot)
<li>Slippery Sheet Bend
<li>Double Carrick Bend
<li>Two Half-Hitches
<li>Timber Hitch
<li>Clove Hitch
<li>Bowline
<li>Man-Harness Knot
<li>Packer's Knot
<li>Sheepshank
<li>Bowline on a Bight
<li>Scaffold Hitch
<li>Tautline Hitch</ol><p>

<li>After showing how to tie the knots in Requirement Number 2, submit a knot-board to your Counselor showing all the knots.<p>

<li>Show and explain the knots to be applied in making the following:
<ol type=a>
<li>Constructing a pergola
<li>Arches and gateways
<li>Repairing the broken leg of a chair
<li>Tying bundles of firewood
<li>Make a 20-foot ladder with wooden rungs</ol></ol>

			
